text: The process p¯p →γ +jet+X is studied using 1.0 fb−1 of data collected by the D0 detector at the
label: BODY

text: Fermilab Tevatron p¯p collider at a center-of-mass energy √
label: BODY

text: s =1.96 TeV. Photons are reconstructed in
label: BODY

text: the central rapidity region |yγ|<1.0 with transverse momenta in the range 30<pγ
label: BODY

text: T <400 GeV while
label: BODY

text: jets are reconstructed in either the central |yjet|<0.8 or forward 1.5<|yjet|<2.5 rapidity intervals
label: BODY

text: with pjet
label: BODY

text: T > 15 GeV. The diﬀerential cross section d3σ/dpγ
label: BODY

text: T dyγdyjet is measured as a function of pγ
label: BODY

text: in four regions, diﬀering by the relative orientations of the photon and the jet in rapidity. Ratios
label: BODY

text: between the diﬀerential cross sections in each region are also presented. Next-to-leading order QCD
label: BODY

text: predictions using diﬀerent parameterizations of parton distribution functions and theoretical scale
label: BODY

text: choices are compared to the data. The predictions do not simultaneously describe the measured
label: BODY

text: normalization and pγ
label: BODY

text: T dependence of the cross section in the four measured regions.

text: the ﬁnal state is a powerful probe of the dynamics of
label: BODY

text: hard QCD interactions [1–6]. Diﬀerent angular conﬁg-
label: BODY

text: urations between the photon and the jets can be used
label: BODY

text: to extend inclusive photon production measurements [7–
label: BODY

text: 10] and simultaneously test the underlying dynamics of
label: BODY

text: QCD hard-scattering subprocesses in diﬀerent regions of
label: BODY

text: parton momentum fraction x and large hard-scattering
label: BODY

label: BODY

label: BODY

label: BODY

label: BODY
